  "signature": "ed25519:b9e2d4f6a1c3e5b7d9f1a3c5e7b9d1f3a5c7e9b1d3f5a7c9e1b3d5f7a9c1e3b5",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Software must be developed and verified under a formal quality management system with documented version control, issue tracking, and regression testing covering all solver modules used in hemolysis prediction. At MRL 5 this requires at minimum ISO 9001-aligned QMS with traceability to requirements.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (OpenFOAM v9) is managed under a laboratory QMS conforming to ISO 9001. Version control via Git with tagged release commits is in place. Regression test suite of 47 canonical cases passes at each release. Documentation reviewed by independent QA auditor. Achieved level 4 meets the required level 4 for MRL 5 Class III device context."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code verification must include method-of-manufactured-solutions (MMS) tests demonstrating expected spatial and temporal convergence rates for all active discretization schemes. At MRL 5, formal order-of-accuracy verification across at least three mesh refinement levels is required for each governing equation set.",
      "rationale": "MMS tests were conducted for the incompressible Navier-Stokes solver and the scalar hemolysis transport equation. Observed spatial order of accuracy was 1.87 (target 2.0) due to boundary-layer mesh non-uniformities near the impeller hub. Temporal convergence confirmed at second order. The shortfall from expected second-order accuracy on the spatial dimension limits the achieved level to 3, one below the required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be computed on at least three systematically refined meshes using Richardson extrapolation. GCI on the hemolysis index QoI must be below 5% at the operating point of maximum predicted hemolysis. Asymptotic range of convergence must be confirmed.",
      "rationale": "Three meshes (2.1 M, 8.4 M, 33.6 M cells) were generated with refinement ratio r=2. GCI on hemolysis index at the worst-case operating point (6 L/min, 3600 RPM) was 3.2%, within the 5% acceptance threshold. Asymptotic convergence ratio of 0.98 confirms operation within the asymptotic range. Achieved level 4 meets required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis measurements were conducted using the modified index of hemolysis (MIH) protocol on a recirculating loop with bovine blood at 37°C. Flow rates and rotational speeds were controlled to within ±1% of target values. However, blood viscosity variability between donors introduced an estimated ±8% uncertainty in the MIH baseline, which reduces fidelity of the test condition representation relative to the CFD boundary conditions. The achieved level is assessed as 3; the required level for MRL 5 Class III is 4. This gap is noted in the decision rationale."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison must be performed using a validation metric (e.g., E_rel or u_val) that accounts for both experimental and numerical uncertainties. Agreement within combined uncertainty bands at all five operating points is required. A formal hypothesis test or confidence interval must be reported.",
      "rationale": "The relative error metric E_rel was computed at all five flow-speed combinations. Predictions fell within the combined uncertainty interval (95% CI) at four of five points; the fifth point showed marginal exceedance of 1.1× the combined uncertainty. Bayesian model comparison confirmed overall predictive adequacy. Achieved level 4 meets required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI used in validation (modified index of hemolysis, MIH) must be directly mappable to the clinical endpoint (plasma-free hemoglobin rise rate). A documented QoI mapping matrix must demonstrate that no intermediate surrogate transformation introduces unquantified bias.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the modified index of hemolysis (MIH), which is directly linked to plasma-free hemoglobin accumulation via the power-law hemolysis model. The QoI mapping matrix documents the relationship between MIH, NIH, and the clinical threshold of 0.1 g/dL/100 L. No surrogate transformation is required. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must be conducted on a geometry and operating envelope that overlaps with the COU geometry and operating envelope by at least 80% in the parameter space defined by flow rate, rotational speed, and fluid properties. Extrapolation beyond the validation domain must be bounded by sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which matches the COU geometry exactly. Operating conditions covered 4 of 5 COU operating points directly; the fifth point (2 L/min, 4200 RPM) lies at the boundary of the validated envelope. Sensitivity analysis at the boundary point shows hemolysis predictions are monotonically consistent with adjacent validated points. The partial extrapolation limits the achieved level to 3 versus the required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence must be demonstrated by reduction of all residuals to below 1e-5 relative to initial residual for each operating point simulation. Solver round-off error must be shown to be negligible relative to discretization error via double-precision arithmetic confirmation.",
      "rationale": "All simulations were run in double-precision arithmetic. Residuals for continuity, momentum, and hemolysis scalar converged to below 1e-6 at all five operating points. Round-off error estimated at 1e-12 relative magnitude, negligible compared to GCI of 3.2%. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "A documented simulation workflow checklist must be followed by all analysts, with independent peer review of boundary condition setup, mesh quality metrics, and post-processing scripts for each operating point. Evidence of peer review sign-off must be retained.",
      "rationale": "A simulation workflow checklist was developed and applied for all five operating points. Peer review of boundary conditions and post-processing was conducted internally but not by an independent reviewer outside the project team. The absence of fully independent review limits the achieved level to 2, below the required level 3. This gap is flagged as a residual risk in the decision record."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "The hemolysis model form is the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model integrated along Lagrangian particle trajectories. Model form uncertainty was assessed by comparing predictions from three alternative hemolysis model formulations (Arora, Zhang, and Taskin models) across all operating points. The spread among model predictions was 12–18% of the mean MIH value, indicating non-negligible model form uncertainty. A formal Bayesian model averaging was not performed due to insufficient experimental replicates to estimate model weights, which limits the achieved level to 3 versus the required level of 4 at MRL 5. The rationale for requiring level 4 reflects that at MRL 5 with a Class III device, model form uncertainty must be formally bounded rather than descriptively characterized."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters must have documented sources with quantified uncertainty distributions. Monte Carlo propagation of input uncertainty must be performed with at least 500 samples. The 95th percentile of the hemolysis index prediction must remain below the clinical threshold.",
      "rationale": "Input parameters (blood viscosity, density, power-law constants α and β, rotational speed, flow rate) were assigned probability distributions based on literature meta-analysis and experimental characterization. Monte Carlo UQ was performed with 1000 Latin hypercube samples. The 95th percentile MIH across all operating points remained 18% below the clinical threshold of 0.1 g/dL/100 L. Achieved level 4 meets required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "A minimum of three independent experimental replicates per operating point must be available, with inter-replicate variability characterized and reported as a component of the combined uncertainty budget.",
      "rationale": "Experimental data consisted of two replicates per operating point from a single laboratory source (FDA interlaboratory study subset). A third replicate was not available for two of the five operating points due to sample exhaustion. Inter-replicate variability was estimated from the two available replicates and propagated into the uncertainty budget, but the statistical power of this estimate is limited. The achieved level of 2 reflects the insufficient replicate count relative to the required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Boundary conditions applied in the CFD model must be demonstrated to be equivalent to the experimental test conditions within the combined measurement uncertainty. A parameter equivalency table must document each input parameter, its experimental value, its CFD value, and the equivalency tolerance.",
      "rationale": "A parameter equivalency table was prepared covering inlet flow rate, outlet pressure, rotational speed, fluid viscosity, and fluid density. All parameters were matched within the combined measurement uncertainty bounds. The largest deviation was rotational speed, matched to within 0.3% of the target value. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou2-vad-decision",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The aggregate credibility assessment for COU2 at MRL 5 identifies gaps in four factors (Numerical code verification, Test conditions, Relevance of validation activities, Use error, Model form, and Test samples), with achieved levels below required levels. Despite these gaps, the decision team accepts the simulation evidence on the basis that: (1) the hemolysis index predictions remain below the clinical threshold at the 95th percentile of the Monte Carlo UQ ensemble; (2) sensitivity analysis bounds the extrapolation risk at the boundary operating point; (3) the model form uncertainty spread, while not formally averaged, is conservative relative to the clinical margin; and (4) the software QA, discretization error, output comparison, and model inputs factors all meet their required levels. Residual gaps in use error and test samples are noted as conditions for post-market surveillance reassessment. The structured acceptanceCriteria field was not populated for the Model form factor; the rationale narrative describes the basis for the required level, but the formal structured criterion is absent — this constitutes a documentation gap that does not affect the technical adequacy of the evidence but should be remediated prior to regulatory submission.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
